"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934765","Home Office","false","2018-07-12","<p>It is not the Government’s policy to prevent migrant workers from engaging in legal strike action. I am not aware of any case where a migrant worker has had their leave curtailed, or been removed, as a result of engaging in lawful industrial action.</p><p>However, to put the matter beyond doubt, we will shortly be amending the guidance and Immigration Rules for Tier 2 and 5 migrants and their sponsors. This change will make clear that there will be no immigration consequences for any migrant worker who takes part in legal strike action.</p><p>The guidance will be amended as soon as possible, and I will be amending the relevant Immigration Rule at the next available opportunity in the Autumn.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-12T14:55:32.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934765/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934765/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Visas: Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to exclude strike action from limits on unpaid leave for tier-2 visa migrants.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","160786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934766","Home Office","false","2018-07-26","<p>The Government has committed to establishing a Windrush compensation scheme. We are listening to those affected, including through a recent Call for Evidence, which ended on 8 June. We are using that evidence to inform the scope and design of the scheme, including the kinds of loss for which compensation may be paid, and will launch a public consultation on those details shortly.</p><p>The Government has emphasised the importance of putting in place a scheme that works, quickly and carefully. As part of that process the Home Office is mindful of relevant guidance from HM Treasury and from the National Audit Office, which draws on the lessons learned from other compensation arrangements.</p><p>This process will also help us to understand the scope of the scheme and scale of funding required. The Home Office is in discussion with HM Treasury about all budgets, including any provision that is required for the Windrush compensation scheme.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","160672 ; 160673","2018-07-26T14:40:20.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934766/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934766/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much money his Department has provisionally allocated for the Windrush compensation scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","160674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934767","Home Office","false","2018-07-09","<p>We are now able to obtain the information within the cost limit. Of the 73 referrals from MPs received in 2017 34 were received from Conservative members, 32 from Labour, 1 from the Democratic Unionist Party and 1 from the Liberal Democrats. After closer scrutiny five reports were deemed not to have come from Members of Parliament.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-09T16:32:43.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934767/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934767/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Immigration: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2018 to Question 148604 on Immigration: Enforcement, what estimate he has made of the cost of providing information on the number of (a) Members of Parliament and (b) staff working for Members of Parliament that communicated on immigration enforcement hotlines during 2017; and which political parties they belonged to.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","160675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934768","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-09","<p>​The British Government condemned the 1 July attack on a group of Sikhs and Hindus in Jalalabad. On Twitter I described it as &quot;a despicable attack on Afghanistan's historic Sikh and Hindu community&quot;. The UK regularly raises human rights issues with the Government of Afghanistan, including the need to protect the rights of all ethnic and religious groups in line with the constitution. As part of NATO's Resolute Support Mission, the UK supports the Afghan National Defence and Security Forces in its efforts to improve security for all communities in Afghanistan.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-07-09T15:44:15.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934768/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934768/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-04","Afghanistan: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the Afghanistan Government on the protection of Afghan Sikhs.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","160804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934769","Prime Minister","false","2018-07-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by the Minister for Europe and the Americas, my right hon. Friend the Member for Rutland and Melton (Sir Alan Duncan) to my right hon. Friend the Member for Rushcliffe (Mr Kenneth Clarke) on 2 July 2018 (Volume 644, Column 26).</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2018-07-12T15:07:18.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934769/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934769/answer",,,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-07-04","Detainees: Inhuman Treatment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if the Government will take steps to establish an independent public inquiry into UK complicity in torture and rendition.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","160787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934770","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-09","<p>The Department has regular accountability review meetings with the NHS Business Service Authority (BSA) to discuss their performance including for prescription pricing and payments to pharmacies. The NHS BSA is obliged to report on a monthly basis against key performance indicators which cover timeliness of service delivery; and quality (accuracy) of service delivery for the National Health Service prescription services. The latest published data for accuracy of prescription processing affecting payment to pharmacies, shows a high and continuing improving level of accuracy. This is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/pharmacies-gp-practices-and-appliance-contractors/payments-and-pricing/how-we-process-prescriptions" target="_blank">https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/pharmacies-gp-practices-and-appliance-contractors/payments-and-pricing/how-we-process-prescriptions</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","160806","2018-07-09T14:21:28.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934770/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934770/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-04","Pharmacy: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what discussions he has had with the NHS Business Services Authority on payments to pharmacists.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","160805"
