"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934819","Department for Education","false","2018-07-12","<p>We are reforming Functional Skills to make sure their content addresses the skills that employers have told us they need. Over 500 employers of varying sizes responded to the employer survey or participated in follow-up interviews[1]. These results have been used to reform the content of Functional Skills[2] (published in February this year) so they will deliver what employers require.</p><p> </p><p>Good communication skills was a key skillset identified by employers, especially oral communication. Speaking and listening have always been a key part of the English Functional Skills qualification, but the reformed qualification will include the term ‘communicating’ to recognise that learners, especially those with disabilities, may communicate in different ways.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1]<a href="http://www.pyetait.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Employer-Consultation-final-report2.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.pyetait.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Employer-Consultation-final-report2.pdf</a>.</p><p>[2] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/functional-skills-subject-content-english" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/functional-skills-subject-content-english</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-07-12T13:44:40.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934819/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934819/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934819/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-04","Communication Skills: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has to ensure that communication skills identified as needed for the workplace are recognised in the criteria for the Functional Skills qualifications.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","160727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934820","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-11","<p>The outcome of NHS England’s latest Specialised Commissioning prioritisation round was published on 7 July 2018. Further details can be found on NHS England’s website and accessed via the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/2018/07/thousands-of-patients-to-benefit-from-innovative-new-treatments-on-the-nhs/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/2018/07/thousands-of-patients-to-benefit-from-innovative-new-treatments-on-the-nhs/</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-11T12:57:01.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934820/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934820/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934820/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-04","Clinical Priorities Advisory Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 27 March to Question 134482 on the Clinical Priorities Advisory Group, when NHS England plans to communicate the results of the Specialised Services Commissioning Committee meeting held on 19 June 2018.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","160701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934821","Department for International Development","false","2018-07-11","<p>The Department for International Development is playing a proactive role in shaping the content of the outcome document for the forthcoming UNGA High Level Meeting on Tuberculosis, which is still being negotiated. The UK’s position is that the outcome document must be consistent with agreed international treaties on intellectual property rights, notably TRIPS and the Doha Declaration on Public Health (2001). In line with the declaration, we support developing countries in utilising TRIPS flexibilities in the case of national health emergencies such as pandemics.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-11T14:41:49.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934821/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934821/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934821/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-07-04","Developing Countries: Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans the Government has to seek the inclusion of an affirmation of the right of all countries to use TRIPS flexibilities to ensure access affordable medicines in the UN tuberculosis high level meeting outcome document.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","160670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934822","Department for Education","false","2018-07-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 4 July 2018 to Question 159051:</p><p><a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-06-29/159051/" target="_blank">https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-06-29/159051/</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-07-12T13:49:32.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934822/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934822/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934822/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-04","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of funding for the provision of high quality social care services for disabled children throughout England.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","160824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-10","<p>This is a Guest of Government visit and as with all visits of this nature, associated costs will be published on the gov.uk website. We will of course work with the police to support the policing operation around President Trump's visit. We will consider any request for special grant funding we receive in line with our normal processes.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-07-10T09:45:41.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823/answer/previousversion/68504","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/members/343","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934823/answer/previousversion/68504",,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-04","USA: State Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will ask the US Government to cover the cost to Thames Valley Police of policing any visit to Oxfordshire by the US President during his upcoming visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","160825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934824","Home Office","false","2018-07-18","<p>There was an 11% increase in police recorded offences involving firearms (excluding air weapons) in the year ending December 2017 compared with the previous year. This continues an upward trend which began in 2014. There is evidence that part, but not all, of the increase is due to specific improvements in the recording of firearms offences. Despite recent increases, offences are still 32% below a decade ago (year ending March 2007) and 43% lower than their peak in 2005/6.</p><p>Our new Serious Violence Strategy explains how changes in the drugs market are driving the recent increase in serious violence, including gun crime, and sets out a major programme of work to tackle this issue.</p><p>In respect of gun crime, we are actively strengthening controls on legally owned firearms to mitigate the risk of them falling into criminal hands. We have included measures in our Offensive Weapons Bill to ban certain high energy rifles, rapid firing rifles and bump stocks. Other measures include greater regulation of antique firearms, new offences on converting imitation firearms and selling defectively deactivated firearms, improving the controls on firearms dealers and establishing a new National Firearms Threat Centre to coordinate law enforcement activity to disrupt the supply of illegal firearms.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-07-18T15:42:25.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934824/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934824/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Firearms: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment he has made of trends in the use of firearms to commit crimes in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","160780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934825","Home Office","false","2018-07-10","<p>The Home Office only publishes data on the number of returns from the UK, by destination, in table rt_05 of the <em>Immigration Statistics</em> release.</p><p>The data shows that in 2017, there were 172 returns from the UK to Afghanistan.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-10T09:17:46.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934825/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934825/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Deportation: Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were subject to removal by the Home Office to Afghanistan in 2017.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","160781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934826","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-09","<p>The information is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-07-09T14:34:55.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934826/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934826/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-04","Mental Health Services: Restraint Techniques","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people with mental health diagnoses have died as a result of being placed physical restraint in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","160782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-11","<p>The Homelessness Reduction Act 2017 has changed the point at which a local authority must accept a duty to an applicant, and the duties that are owed. We will continue to report on applications on which the 'main' homelessness duty is accepted, which will be equivalent and comparable to the data on acceptances reported until now. In addition we will be able to report where local authorities have accepted a duty to prevent homelessness and to relieve homelessness, which are new duties owed to people irrespective of priority need or intentional homelessness.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-07-11T11:42:42.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827/answer/previousversion/68356","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/members/1530","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934827/answer/previousversion/68356",,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-04","Homelessness: Temporary Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 4 July to Question 158161, if he will set out the ways in which new headline figures showing the number of homeless acceptances will be not be comparable with existing statistics published by his Department.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","160692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934828","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-12","<p>I have regular discussions with the Home Secretary and other Cabinet colleagues on a number of matters.</p><p> </p><p>The UK Government’s approach to drugs remains clear - we must prevent drug use in our communities and support people through treatment and recovery. Combatting drug-related crime in Scotland is a matter for the Scottish Government, who we will continue to work closely with.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-12T09:37:12.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934828/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934828/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-07-04","Crime: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the Home Secretary on drug-related crime in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934829","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>While I regularly meet with Cabinet colleagues, including the Secretary of State for Transport, to discuss a wide range of issues that relate to Scotland, the responsibility for transport provision in Scotland is primarily devolved to the Scottish Government.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-11T09:45:26.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934829/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934829/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-07-04","Transport: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on transport provision in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934830","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>I meet regularly with the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs to discuss a wide range of issues. We recently discussed key issues of importance to Scottish farming when we both attended the Royal Highland Show in Edinburgh and had the opportunity to speak directly to representatives of the industry.</p><p> </p><p>I fully appreciate the importance of CAP support to Scottish farmers which is why I am pleased that this Government has made a commitment that the amount we allocate to farming support - in cash terms - will be protected until the end of this Parliament.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-11T09:47:27.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934830/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934830/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-07-04","Agriculture: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Environment, Food, and Rural Affairs on the replacement of CAP funding for Scottish farmers after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934831","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I provided to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-02-26/129558/" target="_blank">129558</a> on 1 March 2018.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-07-12T14:51:57.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934831/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934831/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-04","Universal Credit: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the effect on low-income families of the roll-out of universal credit in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934832","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-11","<p>We have not estimated costs of Personal Independence Payments at this level. As a result this information is not available for Scotland only and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-07-11T14:42:01.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934832/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934832/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-04","Personal Independence Payment: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the cost to the public purse of the Government’s reassessment of people who may be eligible for personal independence payments in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934833","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>Cabinet meets regularly to discuss a range of issues relating to our departure from the European Union. In relation to the replacement of EU structural funds, the Government has committed to creating a UK Shared Prosperity Fund which will boost productivity and reduce inequalities across our four nations.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016, the Chancellor confirmed that the Government will guarantee EU funding for structural and investment fund projects signed after the Autumn Statement and which continue after we have left the EU. Further to this, the Withdrawal Agreement ensures that UK entities’ right to participate in EU programmes will be unaffected by the UK’s withdrawal from the EU for the lifetime of projects financed by the current Multi-annual Financial Framework. UK based organisations and individuals will be able to bid for funding, participate in and lead consortia, until programme closure. This settlement, once agreed as part of the Withdrawal Treaty, will supersede the requirement for the domestic guarantee announced by the Government in 2016. UK organisations should continue to bid for EU funding with the assurance that payments will continue after our departure from the EU.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-11T09:49:21.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934833/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934833/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-07-04","EU Grants and Loans: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the (a) Chancellor of the Exchequer and (b) Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union on the replacing of EU structural funding after the transition period after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934834","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-12","<p>I have regular contact with Cabinet colleagues around the Industrial Strategy and how we can maximise the potential for Scotland. I have also had many conversations with Keith Brown regarding the industrial strategy and will continue to have such conversations with the relevant ministers in the newly formed Scottish Government Cabinet. The UK Government will continue to work collaboratively with the Scottish Government to maximise the potential of the Industrial Strategy in Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-12T09:38:57.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934834/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934834/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-07-04","Industry: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues and Ministers of the Scottish Government on the effect of the UK Government’s industrial strategy on Scotland.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934835","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-09","<p>The Ministry of Defence is reviewing a range of options to ensure a form of voluntary veterans' identification is made available. We will make a further announcement later this year.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-07-09T15:56:46.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934835/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934835/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-04","Veterans: Identity Cards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Prime Minister's announcement last year of plans to provide 2.5 million former armed forces personnel cards to identify them as veterans (a) what steps have been taken to provide those personnel cards; and whether his Department has set a timeline for when those personnel cards will be issued.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","160662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934836","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-12","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the answer given to Question UIN 157806 on 4 July 2018.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-07-12T15:37:44.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934836/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934836/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-04","Aerials: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to regulate the placement of base station antennae.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","160785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934837","Department for International Development","false","2018-07-10","<p>Information on UK aid spending by country is available in the annual Statistics on International Development publication (available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-on-international-development" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-on-international-development</a>).</p><p>The table below shows published figures on DFID’s bilateral official development assistance (ODA) spend in Malawi from 2009-2016.</p><p>DFID bilateral ODA to Malawi, £ million:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>DFID Bilateral ODA to Malawi</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>68</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>61</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>117</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>106</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>51</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>75</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>94</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Statistics on International Development</p><p> </p><p>Further information on DFID’s results achieved, spending, performance and efficiency can be found in its Annual Reports (available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-annual-report-2011-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-annual-report-2011-2012</a>).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-07-10T15:42:01.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934837/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934837/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-07-04","Malawi: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department has spent on aid projects in Malawi in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934838","Home Office","false","2018-08-21","<p>A Windrush case is completed when the Home Office issues and despatches a document to an individual, confirming their status or the outcome of their application.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-08-21T13:44:05.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934838/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934838/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 4 July 2018 to Question 149583 on Immigration: Windrush Generation, how the Taskforce establishes when a case has been completed.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","160676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934839","Home Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>The data requested is not available. Information relating to individual Windrush migrants is not recorded by constituency.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-11T10:17:49.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934839/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934839/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Windrush generation cases there are in (a) North Lanarkshire and (b) Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill constituency.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","160818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934840","Home Office","false","2018-07-09","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-09T16:31:35.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934840/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934840/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-04","Undocumented Workers: Arrests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2018 to Question 157125 on Undocumented Workers, how many people have been arrested for the offence of illegal working since the introduction of that offence.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","160743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934841","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-11","<p>The Taskforce has a key role in informing and shaping the Government’s response to the company’s liquidation, but it is not a review group and will not publish recommendations. The Taskforce has been focused on taking swift action to mitigate the impacts on the small business supply chain, to support employees and apprenticeships find new employment and for the Taskforce members to help disseminate useful information to their respective shareholders. This has already led to useful collaborations, particularly in relation to work to ensure a swift transaction of construction contracts from Carillion to new contractors to minimise disruptions.</p><p> </p><p>The Taskforce has delivered a range of supportive measures, which include provision made by the Banks of nearly £1bn of support to those affected; Government has made available through the British Business Bank support of up to £100 million to small businesses, through their delivery partners, using the Enterprise Finance Guarantee. HMRC are also helping businesses facing genuine difficulty paying their tax bills through the Business Payment Support Service (BPSS) by offering a range of practical advice and guidance.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-07-11T14:58:42.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934841/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934841/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-04","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 4 July to Question 158694 on Carillion: contracts, if his Department will publish the recommendations of the Government taskforce on how best to mitigate the impact of Carillion’s insolvency.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","160693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934842","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-09","<p>MHCLG takes correspondence very seriously. We have made a number of procedural changes during the course of 2018, and these have underpinned a significant, sustained improvement in our performance. We continue to seek and implement ways to ensure that responses are provided within the target time.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-07-09T15:36:04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934842/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934842/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-04","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that responses to correspondence from hon. Members are provided within the target time.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","160688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934843","Cabinet Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>Commonwealth citizens legally resident in the UK have full voting rights. In British nationality law, a Commonwealth citizen is a person who is either a British national or a national of a country listed in Schedule 3 of the British Nationality Act 1981. The British Nationality (The Gambia) Order 2018 has now come into force and amends Schedule 3 to reflect The Gambia rejoining the Commonwealth. Citizens of The Gambia can now register to vote in the UK.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-07-11T13:49:58.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934843/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934843/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-07-04","Voting Rights: Gambia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when citizens of The Gambia resident in the UK with leave to remain will be permitted to register as UK electors following that country re-joining the Commonwealth on 8 February 2018.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","160737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934844","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-12","<p>General practitioners and primary care teams have a crucial role in supporting the identification of perinatal mental illness and treatment, and are part of an integrated pathway of services. This includes monitoring early onset conditions, providing pre-conception counselling and referring women to specialist mental health services, including Improving Access to Psychological Therapies and specialist perinatal community teams, if necessary.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is investing £63 million between 2016/17 and 2018/19 to support development of specialist perinatal mental health community services across England as part of a £365 million transformation programme of perinatal mental health services to 2020/21. Local teams work in close partnership with wider system partners, including primary care, to provide care and treatment to women with perinatal mental illness.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has also invested in multidisciplinary perinatal mental health clinical networks which include general practitioners. The networks drive forward change, focusing on collaborative working. The networks develop local, integrated pathways and support early identification of those at risk of mental illness in the perinatal period, enabling better outcomes for women in all communities.</p><p> </p><p>Targeted funding of £1.2 million was provided in 2017 to enable the training of primary care, maternity and mental health staff to increase awareness and skills related to perinatal mental health.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-07-12T11:42:03.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934844/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934844/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-04","Pregnancy: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding was allocated to increase the effectiveness of GPs in identifying perinatal mental health problems in mothers in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","160732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934845","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-10","<p>The Department is considering its research plans on matters covered by building regulations, in the light of the recommendations of the Independent Review of Building Regulations and Fire Safety by Dame Judith Hackitt.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2018-07-10T10:19:46.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934845/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934845/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-04","Housing: Construction Methods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2018 to Question 147325, whether his Department plans undertake research into modern methods of construction.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","160689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934846","Department for International Development","false","2018-07-11","<p>The Global Polio Eradication Initiative has been an extraordinary success story with cases being reduced from 350,000 a year in 125 countries in 1988, to 22 last year with only 3 countries not yet declared polio-free. The UK has supported this effort with a current spend of £453 million since 2010, and a cumulative investment of £1.3 billion since 1988. The UK continues to be a staunch supporter of the eradication effort.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-11T14:40:24.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934846/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934846/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-07-04","Developing Countries: Poliomyelitis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much funding has been allocated by her Department for the eradication of polio globally since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","160733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934847","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-12","<p>Both the Government and the Data and Communications Company (DCC) have consulted extensively on the enrolment and adoption of SMETS1 meters.</p><p>Government consultations are available online here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/enrolment-of-smets1-meter-cohorts-with-the-data-communications-company" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/enrolment-of-smets1-meter-cohorts-with-the-data-communications-company</a>; <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/maximising-interoperability-for-first-generation-smets1-smart-meters" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/maximising-interoperability-for-first-generation-smets1-smart-meters</a>.</p><p>DCC enrolment and adoption consultations are available online here: <a href="https://www.smartdcc.co.uk/about-dcc/future-service-development/enrolment-and-adoption" target="_blank">https://www.smartdcc.co.uk/about-dcc/future-service-development/enrolment-and-adoption</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has committed to producing an annual report on the smart meter roll-out and, upon publication, will place the 2018 copy in the Libraries of the House. This will include progress towards moving SMETS1 meters into the national communications infrastructure to enable consumers to retain their smart services upon switching.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-07-12T12:50:47.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934847/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934847/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 22 May 2018 to Question 146730 on energy: meters, whether his Department expects the Data and Communications Company to consult on the development of the solution to move SMETS1 meters onto the national communications infrastructure to enable consumers to retain their smart services upon switching; and whether that solution will be reported to Parliament when it is finalised.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","160690"
