"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934191","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-11","<p>We are undertaking a review of Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) performance in the Aid Transparency Index. As part of this, the FCO is in discussion with 'Publish What You Fund', and other Whitehall Departments. These discussions, consultations with the aid transparency community experts and our ongoing programme of work towards the Government target to be “Good” or “Very Good” by 2020, have identified a number of areas for improvement in both our data production and programme documentation.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-07-11T14:06:17.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934191/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934191/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-03","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, following the publication of the 2018 Aid Transparency Index, what steps his Department is taking to improve the transparency of the Official Development Assistance for which it is responsible.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","160284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934192","Department for International Development","false","2018-07-10","<p>DFID has helped develop guidance on publishing to the International Aid Transparency Initiative open data standard (IATI), and continues to provide advice and tailored training to other government departments. The Department hosted transparency workshops in 2016, 2017, and again in July 2018. Transparency is regularly discussed at the cross-Whitehall Official Development Assistance (ODA) Ministerial meetings, which the Secretary of State co-Chairs. Transparency is also discussed at the regular cross-Government Senior Officials Group on ODA and also covered at operational level at cross-Government ODA Learning Days.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-07-10T15:45:13.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934192/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934192/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-07-03","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, following the publication of the 2018 Aid Transparency Index, what steps her Department is taking to meet its goal of helping all departments to achieve a good or very good rating in that index by 2020.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","160285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934193","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-06","<p>The number of Future Reserves 2020 (FR20) Service personnel leaving to join the UK Regular Forces over the last five years is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>250</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>340</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>440</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>520</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>490</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>The figures only include direct transfers from the FR20 population. Figures do not include cadets leaving the University Officer Training Corps, University Air Squadron and University Royal Navy Unit to join the UK Regular forces.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Numbers are rounded to the nearest 10, though numbers ending in a 5 have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-07-06T13:09:38.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934193/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934193/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-03","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of reservists that have joined the regular armed forces in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","160356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934194","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-06","<p>Of the 166 local authorities with a Housing Revenue Account, 104 are in an area of high affordability pressure and are eligible to bid for the additional borrowing programme (63 per cent). A list of eligible authorities is contained in the bidding prospectus.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-07-06T13:17:42.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934194/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934194/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-03","Housing Revenue Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many councils are eligible to bid for additional housing revenue account borrowing in each region.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","160268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934195","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-06","<p>On 26 June the Secretary of State invited local authorities in high affordability pressure areas to bid for the £1 billion additional borrowing programme. The prospectus inviting bids sets out which local authorities are eligible to bid. Chester and Cheshire West Borough Council is not eligible to bid as it does not meet the definition of affordability pressure as set out in the prospectus.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-07-06T13:18:05.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934195/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934195/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-03","Housing Revenue Accounts: Cheshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether Cheshire West and Chester Council is eligible to bid for additional housing revenue account borrowing.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","160269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934196","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-11","<p>There are no Disability Assessors employed at Bangor Assessment Centre.</p><p> </p><p>Capita use the centre to carry out Personal Independence Payment consultations. They have 8 Disability Assessors available to cover Bangor and consultations are conducted in the assessment centre and claimants’ homes.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-07-11T09:54:26.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934196/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934196/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-03","Personal Independence Payment: Bangor","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many assessors were employed at the Bangor Personal Independence Payment assessment centre as of 1 July 2018.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","160111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934197","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-11","<p>Capita utilise the one-room facility at Bangor Assessment Centre five days a week. There are eight bookable slots in clinic per day, and 40 per week.</p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-07-11T14:40:23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934197/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934197/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-03","Personal Independence Payment: Bangor","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many assessments on average are able to be carried out each (a) day and (b) week at in the Personal Indepedence Payment assessment centre in Bangor.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","160112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934198","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-06","<p>The metric that is used to assess whether a local authority is in an area of high affordability pressure is whether it has a difference of £50, or more, per week between average social and private rents at the local authority level. As this data is only available at the local authority level, bids can not be accepted in respect of geographic areas that are smaller than local authority areas.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-07-06T13:18:45.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934198/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934198/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-03","Housing Revenue Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether when determining the high affordability pressure criterion of the additional housing revenue account borrowing programme prospectus he accounts for variations within local authority areas which mean some towns and cities face more significant cost pressures than the local average.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","160270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934199","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-11","<p>Between April and June 2018 the average waiting time between the arrival of a case at Capita and an appointment taking place at Bangor Assessment Centre was 42 working days.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-07-11T14:46:41.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934199/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934199/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-03","Personal Independence Payment: Bangor","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average waiting time has been for an appointment with a Personal Independence Payment assessor at  Bangor assessment centre over the last three months.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","160113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-10","<p>104 of the 166 local authorities with a Housing Revenue Account are in an area of high affordability pressure and so are eligible to bid for the additional borrowing programme. We will review how authorities respond to this opportunity, and consider whether any further action is needed.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-07-10T16:42:29.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200/answer","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200/answer/previousversion/68088","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/members/4007","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934200/answer/previousversion/68088",,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-03","Housing Revenue Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to extend to all local authorities the permission to bid for additional housing revenue account borrowing to build new council housing.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","160271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934201","Women and Equalities","false","2018-07-09","<p>GEO is working on what the interim funding will cover and how it will be delivered. The Minister for Women and Equalities is keen that the delivery model and the communications around it help reinforce that political parties have the prime responsibility for supporting their disabled candidates. Further details will be announced in due course.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-07-09T13:42:35.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934201/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934201/answer",,,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-07-03","Access to Elected Office for Disabled People Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, pursuant to the Answers of 2 July 2018 to Questions 158205 and 158206, on Access to Elected Office Fund, how she plans to promote the existence of the £250,000 of new funding announced on 17 May 2018; and such planned promotion is expected to start.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","160175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934202","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-06","<p>​We offer consular assistance to British nationals when arrested and/or detained overseas and this ceases when the individual has been released or no longer needs our assistance.</p><p>We do not keep records of where a British national travels onto once they are released or consular assistance is no longer needed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-07-06T12:09:56.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934202/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/934202/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-03","Democratic Republic of Congo: Diplomatic Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2018 to Question 153716, how many of those British nationals who received consular assistance from HM Government due to arrest and/or detention in the Democratic Republic of Congo since 2010 have been returned to the UK.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","160057"
